text.tspan: To summarize the project, I enjoyed looking through Ancestry
records and creating this presentation. Although I wanted to do
more than the minimum in the choice board, this project took a
long time to make, so I would most likely not get it done in that
case. My family tree on my dad's side is all from Georgia, with
my dad being the only current US ancestor on his side (as far as
I know). Some cities some of those ancestors were born in were
Tbilisi, Chiatura, and a bunch of the small villages on the
mountains, such as the one my grandmother currently lives in,
Tskhrukveti. My mother's side had miles of hints and records to
base off of, so research was way easier. For the most part, my
maternal-maternal side is from Liebenthal and Herzog
Russia, and my maternal-paternal side is from Canada
(specifically Quebec) and even goes back to France (specifically
Bourgogne). This was a super fun project, and it was especially
interesting to see the roots of my mom.
